race.comment: EXCEED THE BOOM (1) resumed with a solid effort at Belmont and then beaten just 1.6L here, and didn't have much luck here from a wide gate. He's raced at Group and Stakes level and has more up his sleeve. Sets the standard for the promising newcomers. BRUTALLY BRAD (5) debuts and brings a big Lark Hill trial win. She's speedy and can use an inside gate. The gun hoop is booked and the filly is feared. HOT AND HIGH (6) debuts and Chris Parnham sticks from a recent Belmont trial win. She looks progressive and ready to race well. SISTER MARY (4) resumes and jumps from the inside barrier. Her recent Belmont trial placing suggests she will come back improved. She didn't have much luck with wide draws in her brief initial preparation.
